<figureCitation id="6F1875199A2338E30712CF3E687F0158" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Arecophila gulubiicola (BRIP 23002 a, holotype) A, B herbarium material with label C ascomata on the host D, E sections of ascomata F paraphyses G-J asci K peridium L, M wedge-shaped, J + apical ring bluing in Melzer's reagent N-Q ascospores. Scale bars: 50 μm (D, E); 5 μm (F-Q)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.79475.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672050" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="454E7BAC1D9565B6FC23D0666F2973E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="description">
<paragraph id="7D697A9FE60D5DE4A9038497695DF9A3" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="235BFA8448383C55AEF9530E4876AFDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="9B38BB6842D3C15A5B9D18D0F115B9AB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Saprobic</emphasis>
on dead trunk of 
<taxonomicName id="A54735C9C510D2D3370ED2A938A486B6" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Gulubia" higherTaxonomySource="IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gulubia costata" order="Arecales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis id="B6958AB92080468F4117DEFC171EBAD1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Gulubia costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Becc.) Becc. 
<emphasis id="EC99D28B467A1D8EB8894E4EB7DE143F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Sexual morph</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="94DF14DB2224BE6D20F68CF8C6877DA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Ascomata</emphasis>
290-400 
<normalizedToken id="93CC2D782AF9C51A95068B01681E1AE3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
140-190 
<normalizedToken id="D0873B6BBD2E2AB476C4A7E199CF530E" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="CA65405EA20DA57000D584DCA58831EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x̄</emphasis>
= 336 
<normalizedToken id="B089869829920FD29723E938CFE18D93" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
167 
<normalizedToken id="B76FF6B9AC3737C40FBAA940EB2B5979" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 8), immersed under a clypeus, solitary or clustered, in vertical section, lenticular, with a central ostiole. 
<taxonomicName id="51D53E79044354ED6FAFC3C2FFA04C85" authorityName="Leske" authorityYear="1778" class="Echinoidea" family="Clypeidae" genus="Clypeus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clypeus" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="549A5E9902E6DDFB566472BCBE9E2ECC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Clypeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
raised, oval, blackened areas on the host surface, dome-shaped, well-developed and black. 
<emphasis id="B2C5911668F07F81C3A950AFA19055DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Peridium</emphasis>
25-35 
<normalizedToken id="D7AD3258155FBB958B465ACA4AC17973" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, dense, compressed layers of brown-walled, 
<emphasis id="7765D149622E1F6B8711AFCA33DDCE08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">angular</emphasis>
cells, tightly adhered to the host tissues. 
<emphasis id="BD8D4505C0B495253A2B5F80A8C286F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Paraphyses</emphasis>
2-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="A3F110D82EE3D247C770F53B46BE4079" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, filamentous, hyaline, septate, branched, tapering distally. 
<emphasis id="9F9D7831F6F41C3B312FA6BF4F282DF9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Asci</emphasis>
107-145 
<normalizedToken id="81E4BD74396984568915AF14201FF463" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11-13.5 
<normalizedToken id="1906DBC72EE95DB0E7DE874D1A511237" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="4BF432D19A895C8E97BB30DCA0654295" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x̄</emphasis>
= 114.3 
<normalizedToken id="0EA7B7B7D860AC87D0492AF597673F48" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12.4 
<normalizedToken id="7E452BDBECBB7EA49D9639DA7C2F495F" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 15), 8-spored, unitunicate, cylindrical, short-pedicellate, apically rounded, wedge-shaped, J+, subapical ring, 3-4 
<normalizedToken id="83C872BB5F525A37B72CCA22D598D78B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 
<normalizedToken id="9B668880BC7DA22E2F545029B5105451" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="C2AC4AE7B0608D52C4C125F31B3008EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x̄</emphasis>
=3.5 
<normalizedToken id="912B1BEFF321B1A27B83BD077DDD294E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 
<normalizedToken id="386A4ECB323EFCE78073BB7C69939B94" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 15). 
<emphasis id="13CFD4B789916E5810295CEB69B7D3DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Ascospores</emphasis>
14.5-18.5 
<normalizedToken id="299BAEF591C9F23656D3704BDE257751" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-9 
<normalizedToken id="5362E2E6167DE7185F4A082E4C374079" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="5B0E77514AC4C219F549B0A877B54DCA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">x̄</emphasis>
= 17.4 
<normalizedToken id="41C87D5A405A1B037711AADDB0B9CD95" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6.5 
<normalizedToken id="9CE04D4BBBEEBAC5606C1FF280D808ED" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, n = 25), overlapping uniseriate, ellipsoidal, brown, 2-celled, septate at the centre, constricted at the septum, longitudinal, sulcate striations along the entire spore length, surrounded by a mucilaginous sheath. 
<emphasis id="9438CC77E02F1625CF9C771F09D17E43" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: Undetermined.
</paragraph>
<caption id="0E77B5F2995BFEB825877816C5FC939C" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.79475.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672050" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="C9F3BC3C9084F2DF094D76469B9C0A41" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
