</taxonomicName>
(BRIP 23002a, holotype) 
<emphasis id="19F3DDE8BA753FD678CF7468077691C1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A, B</emphasis>
herbarium material with label 
<emphasis id="9D92A9092E9F986BAE688F55668C126E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">C</emphasis>
ascomata on the host 
<emphasis id="DA6C4E13315655B0A2063F656C456A6F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">D, E</emphasis>
sections of ascomata 
<emphasis id="49092E963E22EEE0FC24DD0CE42D3DAA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">F</emphasis>
paraphyses 
<emphasis id="8F5EF74AAE2CD07921E882618F776D2B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">G-J</emphasis>
asci 
<emphasis id="EB4332B2163C4202A85E0B8BAEE60C3F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">K</emphasis>
peridium 
<emphasis id="9B7FADC6309CCEC6897C3E8064F583C4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">L, M</emphasis>
wedge-shaped, J+ apical ring bluing in 
<normalizedToken id="86664895FEC6DBB1BCB28F93BBE213A4" originalValue="Melzer’s">Melzer's</normalizedToken>
reagent 
<emphasis id="28794885B098CFECCA2C3789191DBECE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">N-Q</emphasis>
ascospores. Scale bars: 50 
<normalizedToken id="2C07E0D68F7F98B947C74E211AAD2D88" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<emphasis id="CBC96D7B85C1598E42A4AD4E7182D2D5" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">D, E</emphasis>
); 5 
