<subSubSection id="82C9FF775464B306531D63348466ED5A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0B63D4905864CE066BC57FEA9EB3C51D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7CCDDB01D6A4C0C0A9EE14846D1C6611" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="85F6901995959103689B6069179C4CF2" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 91" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila gulubiicola" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gulubiicola">
<emphasis id="6C38FE251EC74CCA9D6D07D310B699BD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila gulubiicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has deeply immersed, subglobose to lenticular ascomata with a small or lacking clypeus, cylindrical, short-pedicellate asci with a wedge-shaped, conical, apical ring and ellipsoidal, brown ascospores with wall striations and surrounded by a mucilaginous sheath (
<bibRefCitation id="F0844B0BC37360FDCC2B4C54D1B384A6" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Hyde, KD, 1996. Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63(1/2): 81-100." title="Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 / 2): 81 - 100." year="1996">Hyde 1996</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="61DC7B34FB79E784C498ABCD42739C62" authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C36556A4D9F8C7084C93C0332202A5FF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been introduced as a monospecific genus with the type species 
<taxonomicName id="298A052041B06AFF230ECCB3C514EC82" genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="8B636A9B50298286A7A119E458DA83AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Karun. et al. on dead sheaths of 
<taxonomicName id="1E22914C47812956F6AA2BE208E0B37D" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Miscanthus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miscanthus sinensis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis id="46FDF1FF69AFF7B818F073C9B5707628" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Miscanthus sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="ED5E8C76D55C77F7B880A5B01D1FA5FA" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Miscanthus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) from Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation id="265069B5082F5D2C1300B417665438EA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B20" refString="Hyde, KD, Norphanphoun, C, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Bhat, DJ, Jones, EBG, Bundhun, D, Chen, YJ, Bao, DF, Boonmee, S, Calabon, MS, 2020. Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11(1): 305-1059. https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" title="Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11 (1): 305 - 1059." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" year="2020">Hyde et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). We re-examined both 
<taxonomicName id="6677CE331BF22B16CA222A2FA9E2138B" genus="A." lsidName="A. gulubiicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="gulubiicola">
<emphasis id="73AB949D669C468D6BB2A864E0AD0634" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. gulubiicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3F227C2FFD6AA5C9F230563BF8FB8EDC" genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="E821AA49E3C044A56DA21D7E8C435211" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herbarium specimens and observed that they are congeneric. 
<taxonomicName id="D925C90C35C7630E23B449A32AE01D8D" authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica miscanthi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="F8D20D3052DCBFD500FF1A723BDA59F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has characters that immersed ascoma under a clypeus, unitunicate, cylindrical asci with a J+ apical ring and brown, 2-celled ascospores with longitudinal wall striations and a mucilaginous sheath which are consistent with the generic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="C43106E712EA3A944782A488C4342DE8" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EB8BE6EE8790FDA10092ACF1D0544CFC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName id="16B44BCA7DE1A81630B5056A181B40A4" genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="6C87D37459547B36FEADAD56F26BA3E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was mainly considered by the 
<taxonomicName id="F6095D4F71C402F39E33E9378DD04EC0" genus="A." lsidName="A. bambusae" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis id="7E6812F49B947277AEADBD3479B63EEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(HKUCC 4794) sequences (
<bibRefCitation id="ED0A06ED320D3843B81F206356322B77" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B20" refString="Hyde, KD, Norphanphoun, C, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Bhat, DJ, Jones, EBG, Bundhun, D, Chen, YJ, Bao, DF, Boonmee, S, Calabon, MS, 2020. Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11(1): 305-1059. https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" title="Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11 (1): 305 - 1059." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" year="2020">Hyde et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, HKUCC 4794 is not the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="8275D6F143F99CB0D1FA5772195A759B" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C862C1E527B8FDDA162DC9E158016029" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and cannot be used to represent 
<taxonomicName id="3673F16DE653A37136F9015509D62493" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0B9C07E116C38ED9E47187DF9F2EEC9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In our phylogeny, HKUCC 4794 forms a distinct clade (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A3EC12BF456AE45EFB9962FC63542F20" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogenetic tree, based on a combined ITS, LSU, rpb 2 and β-tubulin gene dataset. Numbers close to each node represent Maximum Likelihood bootstrap values (≥ 75 %) and Bayesian posterior probabilities (≥ 0.95). The hyphen (&quot; - &quot;) means a value lower than 75 % (BS) or 0.95 (PP). New taxa are marked in red. Type materials are marked with T after the strains. The tree is rooted to Achaetomium macrosporum (CBS 532.94), Chaetomium elatum (CBS 374.66) and Sordaria fimicola (CBS 723.96)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.79475.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672047" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">1</figureCitation>
; Clade 2) from the 
<taxonomicName id="828DD6DAA0D665939A06B321A4C8B751" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E396E07A24CB5539C3B385F3B7D42D53" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
representing the clade. Based on morphology and phylogeny, we synonymise 
<taxonomicName id="8C1B7CBFD10478447ADA8908E9F37547" authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5191D9AB40A28B4D5A42CFDBC630F1EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="14DE29D9F898160433C3D9AC255CDA90" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9137EE8B42D963B54CA69E26A4130A9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7E121F1416DAADC827ADD0DA0522E2A8" genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="9BC2CB258C59DED41E60CE69949966FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is accepted as an 
<taxonomicName id="41AD6F8E26307C689EB47B1983E89544" authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="196743AE3051411C30F46027B13515CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="F4ADDBA56246B9936B1C022F10CABB5E" genus="A." lsidName="A. bambusae" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis id="7A198E321F56CC73EB4BD492EE9ECF4B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
needs to be recollected and provided with the phylogenetic affinity in future studies.
</paragraph>
